						<summary>

						<p>Slab fixed in the wall of the Gangamma shrine.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1591, Prabhava, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 10.</hi> may correspond to 1669 A.D., October 23, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>It records the foundation of a grove <hi rend="italic">(vana)</hi> by Ponnama Reḍḍi, Chennā Reḍḍi and Pōṭipāpi Reḍḍi as an offering to please god Sūryanarayana.</p>						

						</summary>
